.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::Script::Tree \- BIP341 Script trees
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module contains implementation of script trees described in
BIP341 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0341.mediawiki>. These
trees are used by taproot and are necessary to build custom taproot scripts.
.SS "Tree leaves"
.IX Subsection "Tree leaves"
Each leaf in the tree is represented with this Perl structure:
.PP
.Vb 5
\&        {
\&                id => integer (optional),
\&                leaf_version => integer,
\&                script => Bitcoin::Crypto::Script instance (or its coercible),
\&        }
.Ve
.PP
Optional \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR is used to identify the leaf in the tree, which is used in
methods like "get_control_block".
.PP
Currently, \f(CW\*(C`leaf_version\*(C'\fR must be equal to
"TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Constants, since other
versions are reserved for future use.
.PP
If the leaf is prehashed or not known, it can be represented as this structure
instead:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&        {
\&                hash => bytestring with prehashed leaf,
\&        }
.Ve
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
\fItree\fR
.IX Subsection "tree"
.PP
\&\fIAvailable in the constructor.\fR
.PP
Internal structure of the tree. This structure represents a binary tree and
must contain an array reference of array or hash references.
.PP
Each level of a tree must be an array reference with up to two values in it.
Each leaf must be a hash with either a prehashed value under \f(CW\*(C`hash\*(C'\fR key
(bytestring or something which can be coerced into a bytestring) or a script to
be hashed represented by keys \f(CW\*(C`leaf_version\*(C'\fR (integer up to 255) and \f(CW\*(C`script\*(C'\fR
(an instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Script or something which can be coerced
into it).
.PP
Example structure:
.PP
.Vb 10
\&        # tree with all scripts known
\&        [
\&                {
\&                        id => 0,
\&                        leaf_version => TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION,
\&                        script => [hex => \*(Aq2071981521ad9fc9036687364118fb6ccd2035b96a423c59c5430e98310a11abe2ac\*(Aq]
\&                },
\&                [
\&                        {
\&                                id => 1,
\&                                leaf_version => TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION,
\&                                script => [hex => \*(Aq20d5094d2dbe9b76e2c245a2b89b6006888952e2faa6a149ae318d69e520617748ac\*(Aq]
\&                        },
\&                        {
\&                                id => 2,
\&                                leaf_version => TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION,
\&                                script => [hex => \*(Aq20c440b462ad48c7a77f94cd4532d8f2119dcebbd7c9764557e62726419b08ad4cac\*(Aq]
\&                        }
\&                ]
\&        ]
.Ve
.PP
Each element may be prehashed, which represents the same tree, but without
disclosing information about a script:
.PP
.Vb 11
\&        # same tree, but only one script is known and can be executed
\&        [
\&                {hash => [hex => \*(Aqf154e8e8e17c31d3462d7132589ed29353c6fafdb884c5a6e04ea938834f0d9d\*(Aq]},
\&                [
\&                        {
\&                                leaf_version => TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION,
\&                                script => [hex => \*(Aq20d5094d2dbe9b76e2c245a2b89b6006888952e2faa6a149ae318d69e520617748ac\*(Aq]
\&                        },
\&                        {hash => [hex => \*(Aqd7485025fceb78b9ed667db36ed8b8dc7b1f0b307ac167fa516fe4352b9f4ef7\*(Aq]},
\&                ]
\&        ]
.Ve
.SS Methods
.IX Subsection "Methods"
\fInew\fR
.IX Subsection "new"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $tree = $class\->new(%args)
.Ve
.PP
Standard Moo constructor \- see "Attributes".
.PP
\fIfrom_path\fR
.IX Subsection "from_path"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $tree = $class\->from_path($leaf, \e@path)
.Ve
.PP
This static method builds a new \f(CW$tree\fR object from key path \f(CW@path\fR. Key
path represents a script tree by a series of prehashed leaves. \f(CW$leaf\fR is
a tree leaf deserialized from transaction data.
.PP
\&\f(CW@path\fR must only contain bytestrings or their coercibles. Example \f(CW@path\fR
could look like this:
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        (
\&                [hex => \*(Aqd7485025fceb78b9ed667db36ed8b8dc7b1f0b307ac167fa516fe4352b9f4ef7\*(Aq],
\&                [hex => \*(Aqf154e8e8e17c31d3462d7132589ed29353c6fafdb884c5a6e04ea938834f0d9d\*(Aq],
\&        )
.Ve
.PP
\fIget_merkle_root\fR
.IX Subsection "get_merkle_root"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $hash = $tree\->get_merkle_root()
.Ve
.PP
Calculates a merkle root of the script tree. Returns a bytestring which is the
root hash of the tree.
.PP
\fIget_tapleaf_script\fR
.IX Subsection "get_tapleaf_script"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $script = $tree\->get_tapleaf_script($leaf_id)
.Ve
.PP
Returns a tapleaf script of a leaf with given \f(CW$leaf_id\fR. If such leaf does
not exist, an exception is thrown. Returns a script instance.
.PP
\fIget_tapleaf_version\fR
.IX Subsection "get_tapleaf_version"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $int = $tree\->get_tapleaf_version($leaf_id)
.Ve
.PP
Returns a tapleaf version of a leaf with given \f(CW$leaf_id\fR. If such leaf does
not exist, an exception is thrown. Returns an integer.
.PP
\fIget_tapleaf_hash\fR
.IX Subsection "get_tapleaf_hash"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $hash = $tree\->get_tapleaf_hash($leaf_id)
.Ve
.PP
Calculates a tapleaf hash of a leaf with given \f(CW$leaf_id\fR. If such leaf does
not exist, an exception is thrown. Returns a bytestring.
.PP
\fIget_control_block\fR
.IX Subsection "get_control_block"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $block = $tree\->get_control_block($leaf_id, $pubkey)
.Ve
.PP
Builds a taproot control block used in taproot witness data. \f(CW$leaf_id\fR must
be a valid identifier of a leaf existing in the tree. \f(CW$pubkey\fR is a public
key that associated with the address for key path spending. Returns an instance
of Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::ControlBlock.
.PP
\fIget_tree_paths\fR
.IX Subsection "get_tree_paths"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $paths = $tree\->get_tree_paths()
.Ve
.PP
Returns a hash reference of paths for each of leaves in the tree which have an
id. Each path is an array reference \- same as what "from_path" takes as input.
.PP
\fIclear_tree_cache\fR
.IX Subsection "clear_tree_cache"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $tree\->clear_tree_cache()
.Ve
.PP
Clears the internal cache of the tree, forcing recalculation of merkle root and
all leaf hashes. Must be done after the internal structure of the tree
changed.
